Package: OptSLDP
Title: An Optimized Selective Linkage Disequilibrium Pruning Pipeline
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Félicien", "Akohoue", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "akohoue.f@gmail.com",
    comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: Implements OptSLDP, an optimized and extended version of the
    Selective Linkage Disequilibrium Pruning (SLDP) pipeline for genomic
    prediction panel construction. OptSLDP improves on the original SLDP
    algorithm (Zhu et al., 2023) with the following enhancements: chunked
    memory-safe genotype reading; explicit per-chromosome garbage collection;
    multi-trait union protection; covariate-adjusted marginal screening;
    vectorised OLS via BLAS DGEMM; a compiled C++ LD kernel (r^2 computation,
    threshold scanning, greedy pruning); a compiled C++ screening kernel with
    genotype-variance caching across traits; chromosome-streaming screening
    that accumulates only statistics without loading full genotype matrices;
    chromosome-streaming output writing; sequential GDS background pruning
    (one fresh handle per chromosome); and automatic PCA for population
    structure correction via the `n_pcs` parameter (fast GRM
    eigendecomposition on a chromosome-balanced SNP subset;
    optional RSpectra backend for partial eigendecomposition). Supports three input formats (numeric
    dosage, HapMap, VCF), three candidate selection modes (p-value, z-score,
    PVE), positional and LD-based expansion of protected marker sets,
    chromosome-wise background pruning, and stream-cleaning of malformed
    genotype files. Scales automatically from small panels (in-memory) to
    whole-genome sequencing data with more than 10 million SNPs via a
    GDS/SNPRelate disk-backed backend. References:
    Zhu et al. (2023) <doi:10.1186/s12711-023-00843-w>;
    Akohoue et al. (2026) <doi:10.1007/s00122-026-05159-z>.
